90
00:05:35,399 --> 00:05:50,387
We looked at that and we actually took a look at practices in our neighboring districts because, as you remember, this came up because we back in February hadn't started our orientation yet per the typical schedule.

91
00:05:51,168 --> 00:05:56,791
And in particular, the charter schools were already asking people to make decisions about enrollment.

92
00:05:57,877 --> 00:06:11,361
Um, so we spent this meeting sort of deep diving on, um, what various, um, communities around us and, um, including the charter schools are doing, um, based on information that was publicly available.

93
00:06:11,381 --> 00:06:21,364
Um, and in general, most, I'll say most are many communities and certainly, um, the charter schools who, um, take students from Medford.

94
00:06:23,332 --> 00:06:26,475
all get their process going quite early in the year.

95
00:06:26,995 --> 00:06:28,436
Some of them really early.

96
00:06:29,597 --> 00:06:33,361
One of the charter schools first lottery is on January 4th.

97
00:06:33,601 --> 00:06:41,067
So they are moving and grooving long before we have historically started our process.

98
00:06:41,828 --> 00:06:43,129
So we talked a little bit about that.

99
00:06:43,169 --> 00:06:43,870
We talked about

100
00:06:45,549 --> 00:06:48,151
some of the options that we might have.

101
00:06:48,591 --> 00:07:04,264
