1055
01:44:54,598 --> 01:44:55,519
I think Ms.

1056
01:44:55,539 --> 01:44:57,181
Graham's point is well taken that

1057
01:44:57,500 --> 01:45:07,325
we don't just wanna flood the switchboard with calls from families that are concerned because the information on the website doesn't appear to have been updated in the last 24 hours.

1058
01:45:07,926 --> 01:45:16,630
And I think that's fair, but I think we will have to one, look through other systems in terms of keeping people updated at the school building level.

1059
01:45:17,271 --> 01:45:25,555
And frankly, if there's people that are concerned because of the particular susceptibility that may be present within their home,

1060
01:45:25,938 --> 01:45:31,302
I think those families should be in constant contact with the school nurse.

1061
01:45:31,743 --> 01:45:36,947
And they shouldn't worry about the switchboard getting flooded, because we always have time to respond to families.

1062
01:45:37,287 --> 01:45:42,351
The school nursing staff, the school principals, and other building staff are doing it on a daily and hourly basis.

1063
01:45:42,491 --> 01:45:49,636
I am certain that somewhere in Medford right now, there's someone from one of our eight school communities speaking with a family.

1064
01:45:52,189 --> 01:45:58,835
primetime hours for that, but it's a guarantee that that's happening right now, whether it's via email, via phone, via text or what have you.

1065
01:45:59,215 --> 01:46:13,028
