1088
01:48:46,390 --> 01:49:04,736
With that being said, I think that that's the difficulty right now in some of the, you know, concerns that people are bringing up with coverage issues, because that's the kind of umbrella or domino effect that is occurring right now, which the positive rates might be a little low, but the close coverages are a little high.

1089
01:49:04,957 --> 01:49:09,098
So I just needed to say that because the numbers won't be completely valid

1090
01:49:09,605 --> 01:49:14,228
unless we're just reporting on close contacts that are in relationship to Metro Public Schools.

1091
01:49:15,329 --> 01:49:26,376
Yeah, maybe the admin can put their heads together in the next couple of days and give us an email by the end of the week on how best to report this out, this data out to the community by Monday.

1092
01:49:27,737 --> 01:49:27,997
Yes.

1093
01:49:29,659 --> 01:49:30,179
That is fair.

1094
01:49:30,579 --> 01:49:30,799
Okay.

1095
01:49:30,959 --> 01:49:31,460
That is fair.

1096
01:49:31,980 --> 01:49:32,320
Thank you.

1097
01:49:32,541 --> 01:49:33,061
Member Rousseau?

1098
01:49:34,193 --> 01:49:34,514
Thank you.

1099
01:49:34,654 --> 01:49:38,801
I just wanted to respond briefly to miss Lucy's point.

1100
01:49:38,821 --> 01:49:42,087
I think there's like an elephant in the room and that is trust.

1101
01:49:43,527 --> 01:49:48,071
and it is not about whether I trust you all or the rest of the committee trusts you all.

1102
01:49:48,511 --> 01:49:53,074
It's about whether or not the individual families have any reason to trust us.

1103
01:49:53,895 --> 01:50:03,842
And the reason I'm so interested in close contact counts is that we trusted the state, well, we tried to, and then they just moved the goalposts.

1104
01:50:04,922 --> 01:50:08,365
Well, listen, we can move the goalposts on contact tracing too.

1105
01:50:09,195 --> 01:50:14,404
We can go from 10 people on average contact traced and being considered close contacts.

1106
01:50:14,805 --> 01:50:20,174
And this make it, if over time it becomes we only get one or two or zero is the normal.

1107
01:50:21,193 --> 01:50:23,754
for the number of close contacts, that's moving the goalposts.

1108
01:50:24,434 --> 01:50:33,258
So I think families and myself, I have kids and a family, I wanna know that these metrics are consistent.

1109
01:50:33,498 --> 01:50:49,484
I mean, if in September or October, the number of close contacts on average was six, and then in December it's four, and then in February it's two, I'm gonna say trust isn't really appropriate.

1110
01:50:51,057 --> 01:50:53,758
So the elephant in the room is trust.

1111
01:50:54,258 --> 01:51:00,320
All of this is based on trust because families can't go to school, we don't have cameras so we can all watch what's going on.

1112
01:51:01,520 --> 01:51:07,582
And I know I want evidence that makes me think that the trust is deserved.

1113
01:51:07,702 --> 01:51:12,083
It isn't about whether anybody here is a good person or doing their job.

1114
01:51:13,104 --> 01:51:16,605
I think there is data that can be used to make

1115
01:51:17,728 --> 01:51:28,376
giving trust a rational thing, because the state and the federal government, they certainly had fallen flat on any reason to believe government should be trusted.

1116
01:51:28,616 --> 01:51:29,837
And we are government.

1117
01:51:29,917 --> 01:51:33,019
School systems, every employee of a school system is part of the government.

1118
01:51:33,619 --> 01:51:39,663
So I think it behooves us to care about trust explicitly.

1119
01:51:40,344 --> 01:51:43,686
And this, in my mind, is one way to make that happen.

1120
01:51:44,007 --> 01:51:46,068
So that's why I just wanted to point that out.

1121
01:51:48,218 --> 01:51:48,599
Thank you.

