1161
01:55:35,886 --> 01:55:38,787
There are 23 homerooms at the Roberts school.

1162
01:55:39,528 --> 01:55:48,332
And so it's not a situation where we have 23 homeroom teachers that are not available to be in their school.

1163
01:55:48,392 --> 01:55:54,695
So each situation is different and we are responding to each situation as it comes up.

1164
01:55:55,957 --> 01:56:03,764
Throughout this entire process, we have always said that safety, consistency, and equity have been our highest priorities.

1165
01:56:04,404 --> 01:56:07,587
What Medford is doing, no other district is doing.

1166
01:56:09,208 --> 01:56:10,909
They are not testing their staff.

1167
01:56:11,230 --> 01:56:13,311
They're not testing their students.

1168
01:56:14,372 --> 01:56:16,473
We are doing that at this point in time.

1169
01:56:16,954 --> 01:56:19,815
We are prioritizing the health and safety of everyone.

1170
01:56:20,436 --> 01:56:38,525
And with the information that is gathered from the contact tracing, we've identified the staff that need to be quarantined based on the information that's given to the nurses or the board of health members that are doing the contact tracing.

1171
01:56:39,146 --> 01:56:41,807
So that is the response that we have right now.

1172
01:56:42,307 --> 01:56:42,948
If the data

1173
01:56:44,822 --> 01:56:53,486
changes or if there's a significant shift in the data, then we would make an appropriate choice or an appropriate decision at that point in time.

1174
01:56:54,186 --> 01:57:11,993
At this point in time, based on the amount of staff that are not at the Roberts School, that it's five homeroom teachers with two of them scheduled to return by the end of this week, and speaking with the instructional leader of the school, Principal Kirk Johnson,

1175
01:57:13,073 --> 01:57:16,236
And I spoke with him explicitly and had a conversation with him.

1176
01:57:16,636 --> 01:57:19,318
He said that the school can continue to function.

1177
01:57:20,018 --> 01:57:26,043
So I understand that people are very worried and tomorrow will be an opportunity for testing to take place.

1178
01:57:26,483 --> 01:57:28,185
We'll get the results on Wednesday.

1179
01:57:28,205 --> 01:57:41,275
And if the results show that there has been increased activity or uptick, we will be the first ones to communicate that out to the school committee first, and then to the community at large.

1180
01:57:42,035 --> 01:57:55,059
So I think with Wednesday being the day where students are not in person, it gives us that opportunity and a break between Cohort B and Cohort C. And the same is true.

1181
01:57:55,479 --> 01:57:56,540
We worked all weekend.

1182
01:57:57,160 --> 01:57:59,921
The students are tested on Friday for Cohort C.

1183
01:58:01,041 --> 01:58:06,103
And based on the data, we get the data by Saturday or Sunday over the course of the weekend.

1184
01:58:06,643 --> 01:58:10,325
And we take appropriate steps over the course of the weekend.

1185
01:58:10,705 --> 01:58:18,008
So I really don't feel there's anything extra that we can do at this point in time to ensure additional safety.

1186
01:58:18,528 --> 01:58:21,970
We are doing the best we can, given the resources that we have.

1187
01:58:22,490 --> 01:58:29,433
And I'm truly grateful that we are a district that's in a position to be able to say, we're doing the testing.

1188
01:58:30,253 --> 01:58:49,886
not only of staff and not only of teachers, everyone in Medford Public Schools, secretaries, paraprofessionals, custodians, you name it, cafeteria help, any department that you work in Medford Public Schools, you are allowed to be tested and have that personal peace of mind.

1189
01:58:50,666 --> 01:58:53,909
So I really feel like we're doing everything we can do

1190
01:58:55,409 --> 01:59:01,511
And we have the support of the city, the support of Tufts University, Broad Institute, Armstrong Ambulance.

1191
01:59:02,811 --> 01:59:11,093
We thank them every single time because we are so appreciative of all of the support and help that we're getting in Medford.

1192
01:59:11,753 --> 01:59:19,576
And again, if the data is different and the data says we need to make a decision, we will make that decision at the appropriate time.

1193
01:59:20,896 --> 01:59:21,216
Thank you.

1194
01:59:25,260 --> 01:59:27,100
Thank you, Gary.

1195
01:59:31,021 --> 01:59:32,421
Thank you for the opportunity to speak.

1196
01:59:32,761 --> 01:59:33,861
My name is Gary Klein.

1197
01:59:33,921 --> 01:59:38,222
I am the father of a high school student and two recent graduates.

1198
01:59:39,362 --> 01:59:46,104
I do want to thank the whole Medford public school team for all of their hard work.

1199
01:59:46,864 --> 01:59:54,645
And as the father of a student that's learning remotely, I want to particularly thank the teachers because I see how hard they work every day to teach remotely.

1200
01:59:55,902 --> 02:00:03,087
I do want to speak briefly in favor of a cautious approach to bringing kids back, particularly to the high school.

1201
02:00:03,947 --> 02:00:11,412
And my reason for that is that we have worked really hard as a community to keep numbers of cases down.

1202
02:00:12,793 --> 02:00:16,795
We, I think we're very successful over the summer.

1203
02:00:17,216 --> 02:00:24,240
And I think it's very disappointing that the numbers have been so high across the community from since Thanksgiving.

1204
02:00:25,086 --> 02:00:34,230
It looks like there were close to 500 positive cases identified across the community since Thanksgiving, based on the data that's been reported.

1205
02:00:34,711 --> 02:00:45,816
And it looks like we're on track to have close to 1,500 cases between Thanksgiving and the end of the year, which is close to 3% of the entire Medford community.

1206
02:00:46,456 --> 02:00:50,878
And I think it's very sad because we see the light at the end of the tunnel at this point.

1207
02:00:51,821 --> 02:00:53,162
There's a vaccine coming.

1208
02:00:53,862 --> 02:00:55,523
We just have to make it a few more months.

1209
02:00:56,304 --> 02:01:20,217
And I think because the school system is so integrally tied to the community, there is some risk in light of the high numbers that the schools will contribute, whether it's in-school transmission or just because kids are bringing COVID

1210
02:01:20,996 --> 02:01:29,732
from home to the schools or perhaps vice versa, that somehow that there will be a contribution to the high numbers from opening schools.

1211
02:01:30,593 --> 02:01:32,857
And I do think that high school students are different.

1212
02:01:33,294 --> 02:01:41,440
I think the data suggests that there's more risk with older kids of transmission than there is with younger kids.

1213
02:01:41,901 --> 02:01:44,443
I think that kids' behaviors are different in high school.

1214
02:01:44,463 --> 02:01:54,851
And I think if we could just be a little patient, be a little cautious, and make a little extra effort, we'll get to the point where there are vaccines.

1215
02:01:55,271 --> 02:01:59,735
We can open the schools fully without so much anxiety.

1216
02:02:00,471 --> 02:02:02,294
and go back to a normal life.

1217
02:02:02,775 --> 02:02:07,041
I really appreciate the opportunity to speak and hope you'll consider my views.

1218
02:02:07,782 --> 02:02:08,544
Thank you, Mr. Klein.

1219
02:02:08,864 --> 02:02:09,485
We appreciate it.

